Brake Bleeders must always be positioned above the
junction they intend to bleed.  Bleedings purpose is
to purge air from the Brake Fluid.  Air rises in Brake
Fluid.  Without any more facts, I can say you have the
caliper upside down.   Sir.   Happy holidays.
    
